# Main Process Trust Boundary

Per DESIGN.md: **All AI API calls, file I/O, and data persistence happen in the main process. The renderer only sends and receives plain serialisable objects.** **API keys never leave the main process.**

## Rules

- **AI calls** — Only in `electron/services/`. Never call OpenAI, Anthropic, etc. from the renderer.
- **File I/O** — Only in main process. Use IPC to request file ops; return serialisable results.
- **Persistence** — Only `StorageService` (electron-store) in main. Renderer reads/writes via IPC.
- **API keys** — Store encrypted in main. Renderer receives only `hasApiKey: boolean` or equivalent. Never send raw keys over IPC.
- **Serialisation** — IPC payloads must be JSON-serialisable. No functions, Symbols, or class instances.

## Renderer

- Import only from `src/`, Vue, Pinia, Vue Router, VeeValidate, Zod, Tailwind.
- Do not import `electron`, `fs`, `path`, or any Node-only modules.
- All external data comes via `window.api` (typed IPC).
